                <person xml:id="saint-1239" ana="#syriaca-saint">
                    <persName xml:id="name1239-2" xml:lang="en" syriaca-tags="#syriaca-headword">Ezekiel the
          Monk</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name1239-3" xml:lang="en">Ezechial</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name1239-4" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib1239-2">Ézéchiel, moine (de Daqoq)</persName>
                    <persName xml:id="name1239-5" xml:lang="fr-x-fiey" source="#bib1239-1">ÉZÉCHIAL</persName>
                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1239</idno>
                    <idno type="FIEY">159</idno>
                    <idno type="BHS">1210</idno>
                    <sex value="M" source="#bib1239-1">male</sex>
                    <floruit source="#bib1239-1" when="0363" syriaca-computed-start="0363">363</floruit>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1239-1">Suhadii', II, 238-65, d'apres un manuscrit de Kerkouk du xne siecle. Pas dans
BHO.
Fiey, Assyrie chretienne, III, 64-67.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1239">In hagiography: Ezekiel was a monk who was
          born on the same day as the Emperor <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1655">Constantine the Great</persName>. He was a Jew from the tribe of Manasseh who went
            to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/715">Egypt</placeName> and became a disciple
            of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/356">Mar Awgin</persName>. <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/356">Mar Awgin</persName> and his disciples left for
            the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/993">region of
            Adiabene</placeName> and <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/33">Beth
            Garmai</placeName>. They went to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/852">Maḥoze</placeName> and baptized the entire city, after they healed the sick. Ezekiel
          went around the region converting the "Magians." He founded a monastery near Daduq. He
          ended his life in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/718">the region of
            Kirkuk</placeName>.</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1239-2">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="la">Bibliotheca Hagiographica Syriaca</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/649"/>
                        <citedRange unit="entry">1210</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1239-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                        <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">ÉZÉCHIAL</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/650"/>
                        <citedRange unit="entry">159</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                    <title>Shuhadā'</title>
                    <citedRange> II, 238-65</citedRange>
                    <note>From a manuscript from Kirkuk from the 12th century. It is not in the BHO.</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1239-4">
                        <author>
